<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="328" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,315,702]" pageId="27" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,567,593]" pageId="27" pageNumber="328">Remarks</emphasis>
. First reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[556,735,567,594]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="27" pageNumber="328">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McLay" authorityYear="1993" box="[750,873,567,593]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Epigodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="328" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotunda">
<emphasis box="[750,873,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="328">E. rotunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subsequently recorded from the Ogasawara Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[245,312,604,630]" name="Japan" pageId="27" pageNumber="328">Japan</collectingCountry>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Komatsu, H." box="[357,541,603,630]" pageId="27" pageNumber="328" pagination="219 - 277" refId="ref26908" refString="Komatsu, H. (2011) Crabs dredged off the Ogasawara Islands (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura). Memoirs of the National Science Museum, 47, 219 - 277." type="journal article" year="2011">Komatsu (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, and now known from 
<collectingCountry box="[799,905,603,629]" name="Australia" pageId="27" pageNumber="328">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
